A man was shot dead after he allegedly robbed a tourist at the Moyo Zoo Lake restaurant in Johannesburg on Friday evening, police said. Police spokesperson Brig Mathapelo Peters said  the suspect allegedly attacked and robbed a Vietnamese national of his belongings at gunpoint. “It is alleged that a patron inside the restaurant observed the incident and fired shots, fatally wounding the suspect,” Peters said. The suspect’s firearm — with its serial number filed off — was seized by officers. More details were not immediately available. The restaurant could not immediately comment when approached by SowetanLIVE sister publication TimesLIVE.